47angle::Result AllocateTriangleFanBufferFromPool(ContextMtl *context,
48 GLsizei vertexCount,
49 mtl::BufferPool *pool,
50 mtl::BufferRef *bufferOut,
51 uint32_t *offsetOut,
52 uint32_t *numElemsOut)
53{
54 uint32_t numIndices;
55 ANGLE_TRY(mtl::GetTriangleFanIndicesCount(context, vertexCount, &numIndices));
56
57 size_t offset;
58 pool->releaseInFlightBuffers(context);
59 ANGLE_TRY(pool->allocate(context, numIndices * sizeof(uint32_t), nullptr, bufferOut, &offset,
60 nullptr));
61
62 *offsetOut = static_cast<uint32_t>(offset);
63 *numElemsOut = numIndices;
64
65 return angle::Result::Continue;
66}

69 GLsizei indicesToReserve,
70 mtl::BufferPool *pool,

78
79 *offsetOut = static_cast<uint32_t>(offset);
80
81 return angle::Result::Continue;

89std::string ConvertMarkerToCpp(GLsizei length, const char *marker)
90{
91 std::string cppString;
92 if (length == 0)
93 {
94 cppString = marker;
95 }
96 else

100 return cppString;

103// This class constructs line loop's last segment buffer inside begin() method
104// and perform the draw of the line loop's last segment inside destructor
105class LineLoopLastSegmentHelper
106{
107 public:
108 LineLoopLastSegmentHelper() {}
109
110 ~LineLoopLastSegmentHelper()
111 {
112 if (!mLineLoopIndexBuffer)
113 {
114 return;
115 }
116
117 // Draw last segment of line loop here
118 mtl::RenderCommandEncoder *encoder = mContextMtl->getRenderCommandEncoder();
119 ASSERT(encoder);
120 encoder->drawIndexed(MTLPrimitiveTypeLine, 2, MTLIndexTypeUInt32, mLineLoopIndexBuffer, 0);
121 }
122
123 angle::Result begin(const gl::Context *context,
124 mtl::BufferPool *indexBufferPool,
125 GLint firstVertex,
126 GLsizei vertexOrIndexCount,
127 gl::DrawElementsType indexTypeOrNone,
128 const void *indices)
129 {
130 mContextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
131
132 indexBufferPool->releaseInFlightBuffers(mContextMtl);
133 ANGLE_TRY(indexBufferPool->allocate(mContextMtl, 2 * sizeof(uint32_t), nullptr,
134 &mLineLoopIndexBuffer, nullptr, nullptr));
135
136 if (indexTypeOrNone == gl::DrawElementsType::InvalidEnum)
137 {
138 ANGLE_TRY(mContextMtl->getDisplay()->getUtils().generateLineLoopLastSegment(
139 mContextMtl, firstVertex, firstVertex + vertexOrIndexCount - 1,
140 mLineLoopIndexBuffer, 0));
141 }
142 else
143 {
144 ASSERT(firstVertex == 0);
145 ANGLE_TRY(
146 mContextMtl->getDisplay()->getUtils().generateLineLoopLastSegmentFromElementsArray(
147 mContextMtl,
148 {indexTypeOrNone, vertexOrIndexCount, indices, mLineLoopIndexBuffer, 0}));
149 }
150
151 ANGLE_TRY(indexBufferPool->commit(mContextMtl, false));
152
153 return angle::Result::Continue;
154 }
155
156 private:
157 ContextMtl *mContextMtl = nullptr;
158 mtl::BufferRef mLineLoopIndexBuffer;
159};

176angle::Result ContextMtl::initialize()
177{
178 mBlendDesc.reset();
179 mDepthStencilDesc.reset();
180
181 mTriFanIndexBuffer.initialize(this, 0, mtl::kIndexBufferOffsetAlignment,
182 kMaxTriFanLineLoopBuffersPerFrame);
183 mLineLoopIndexBuffer.initialize(this, 0, mtl::kIndexBufferOffsetAlignment,
184 kMaxTriFanLineLoopBuffersPerFrame);
185 mLineLoopLastSegmentIndexBuffer.initialize(this, 2 * sizeof(uint32_t),
186 mtl::kIndexBufferOffsetAlignment,
187 kMaxTriFanLineLoopBuffersPerFrame);
188
189 return angle::Result::Continue;
190}

206{
207 if (ANGLE_UNLIKELY(!mIncompleteTexturesInitialized))
208 {
209 constexpr gl::TextureType supportedTextureTypes[] = {
210 gl::TextureType::_2D, gl::TextureType::_2DArray, gl::TextureType::_3D,
211 gl::TextureType::CubeMap};
212 for (auto texType : supportedTextureTypes)
213 {
214 gl::Texture *texture;
215 ANGLE_UNUSED_VARIABLE(texture);

218 }

220 }
221 return angle::Result::Continue;
222}

236// Drawing methods.
237angle::Result ContextMtl::drawTriFanArraysWithBaseVertex(const gl::Context *context,
238 GLint first,
239 GLsizei count,
240 GLsizei instances)
241{
242 ASSERT((getDisplay()->getFeatures().hasBaseVertexInstancedDraw.enabled));
243
244 uint32_t genIndicesCount;
245 ANGLE_TRY(mtl::GetTriangleFanIndicesCount(this, count, &genIndicesCount));
246
247 size_t indexBufferSize = genIndicesCount * sizeof(uint32_t);
248 // We can reuse the previously generated index buffer if it has more than enough indices
249 // data already.
250 if (mTriFanArraysIndexBuffer == nullptr || mTriFanArraysIndexBuffer->size() < indexBufferSize)
251 {
252 // Re-generate a new index buffer, which the first index will be zero.
253 ANGLE_TRY(
254 mtl::Buffer::MakeBuffer(this, indexBufferSize, nullptr, &mTriFanArraysIndexBuffer));
255 ANGLE_TRY(getDisplay()->getUtils().generateTriFanBufferFromArrays(
256 this, {0, static_cast<uint32_t>(count), mTriFanArraysIndexBuffer, 0}));
257 }
258
259 if (mState.isTransformFeedbackActiveUnpaused())
260 {
261 ANGLE_TRY(setupDraw(context, gl::PrimitiveMode::TriangleFan, first, count, instances,
262 gl::DrawElementsType::InvalidEnum, reinterpret_cast<const void *>(0),
263 true));
264 // Draw with the zero starting index buffer, shift the vertex index using baseVertex
265 // instanced draw:
266 mRenderEncoder.drawIndexedInstancedBaseVertex(MTLPrimitiveTypeTriangle, genIndicesCount,
267 MTLIndexTypeUInt32, mTriFanArraysIndexBuffer,
268 0, instances, first);
269 prepareForTransformFeedbackPassTwo();
270 }
271
272 ANGLE_TRY(setupDraw(context, gl::PrimitiveMode::TriangleFan, first, count, instances,
273 gl::DrawElementsType::InvalidEnum, reinterpret_cast<const void *>(0),
274 false));
275
276 // Draw with the zero starting index buffer, shift the vertex index using baseVertex instanced
277 // draw:
278 mRenderEncoder.drawIndexedInstancedBaseVertex(MTLPrimitiveTypeTriangle, genIndicesCount,
279 MTLIndexTypeUInt32, mTriFanArraysIndexBuffer, 0,
280 instances, first);
281
282 return angle::Result::Continue;
283}
284angle::Result ContextMtl::drawTriFanArraysLegacy(const gl::Context *context,
285 GLint first,
286 GLsizei count,
287 GLsizei instances)
288{
289 // Legacy method is only used for GPU lacking instanced base vertex draw capabilities.
290 mtl::BufferRef genIdxBuffer;
291 uint32_t genIdxBufferOffset;
292 uint32_t genIndicesCount;
293 ANGLE_TRY(AllocateTriangleFanBufferFromPool(this, count, &mTriFanIndexBuffer, &genIdxBuffer,
294 &genIdxBufferOffset, &genIndicesCount));
295 ANGLE_TRY(getDisplay()->getUtils().generateTriFanBufferFromArrays(
296 this, {static_cast<uint32_t>(first), static_cast<uint32_t>(count), genIdxBuffer,
297 genIdxBufferOffset}));
298
299 ANGLE_TRY(mTriFanIndexBuffer.commit(this, false));
300
301 if (mState.isTransformFeedbackActiveUnpaused())
302 {
303 ANGLE_TRY(setupDraw(context, gl::PrimitiveMode::TriangleFan, first, count, instances,
304 gl::DrawElementsType::InvalidEnum, reinterpret_cast<const void *>(0),
305 true));
306
307 execDrawIndexedInstanced(MTLPrimitiveTypeTriangle, genIndicesCount, MTLIndexTypeUInt32,
308 genIdxBuffer, genIdxBufferOffset, instances);
309 prepareForTransformFeedbackPassTwo();
310 }
311 ANGLE_TRY(setupDraw(context, gl::PrimitiveMode::TriangleFan, first, count, instances,
312 gl::DrawElementsType::InvalidEnum, reinterpret_cast<const void *>(0),
313 false));
314
315 execDrawIndexedInstanced(MTLPrimitiveTypeTriangle, genIndicesCount, MTLIndexTypeUInt32,
316 genIdxBuffer, genIdxBufferOffset, instances);
317
318 return angle::Result::Continue;
319}
320angle::Result ContextMtl::drawTriFanArrays(const gl::Context *context,
321 GLint first,
322 GLsizei count,
323 GLsizei instances)
324{
325 if (count <= 3)
326 {
327 return drawArraysInstanced(context, gl::PrimitiveMode::Triangles, first, count, instances);
328 }
329 if (getDisplay()->getFeatures().hasBaseVertexInstancedDraw.enabled)
330 {
331 return drawTriFanArraysWithBaseVertex(context, first, count, instances);
332 }
333 return drawTriFanArraysLegacy(context, first, count, instances);
334}

350angle::Result ContextMtl::drawLineLoopArrays(const gl::Context *context,
351 GLint first,
352 GLsizei count,
353 GLsizei instances)
354{
355 if (instances <= 1)
356 {
357 return drawLineLoopArraysNonInstanced(context, first, count);
358 }
359
360 mtl::BufferRef genIdxBuffer;
361 uint32_t genIdxBufferOffset;
362 uint32_t genIndicesCount = count + 1;
363
364 ANGLE_TRY(AllocateBufferFromPool(this, genIndicesCount, &mLineLoopIndexBuffer, &genIdxBuffer,
365 &genIdxBufferOffset));
366 ANGLE_TRY(getDisplay()->getUtils().generateLineLoopBufferFromArrays(
367 this, {static_cast<uint32_t>(first), static_cast<uint32_t>(count), genIdxBuffer,
368 genIdxBufferOffset}));
369
370 ANGLE_TRY(mLineLoopIndexBuffer.commit(this, false));
371
372 if (mState.isTransformFeedbackActiveUnpaused())
373 {
374 ANGLE_TRY(setupDraw(context, gl::PrimitiveMode::LineLoop, first, count, instances,
375 gl::DrawElementsType::InvalidEnum, nullptr, true));
376
377 execDrawIndexedInstanced(MTLPrimitiveTypeLineStrip, genIndicesCount, MTLIndexTypeUInt32,
378 genIdxBuffer, genIdxBufferOffset, instances);
379 prepareForTransformFeedbackPassTwo();
380 }
381 ANGLE_TRY(setupDraw(context, gl::PrimitiveMode::LineLoop, first, count, instances,
382 gl::DrawElementsType::InvalidEnum, nullptr, false));
383
384 execDrawIndexedInstanced(MTLPrimitiveTypeLineStrip, genIndicesCount, MTLIndexTypeUInt32,
385 genIdxBuffer, genIdxBufferOffset, instances);
386
387 return angle::Result::Continue;
388}

390angle::Result ContextMtl::drawArraysImpl(const gl::Context *context,
391 gl::PrimitiveMode mode,
392 GLint first,
393 GLsizei count,
394 GLsizei instances)
395{
396 // Real instances count. Zero means this is not instanced draw.
397 GLsizei instanceCount = instances ? instances : 1;
398
399 if (mCullAllPolygons && gl::IsPolygonMode(mode))
400 {
401 return angle::Result::Continue;
402 }
403
404 if (mode == gl::PrimitiveMode::TriangleFan)
405 {
406 return drawTriFanArrays(context, first, count, instanceCount);
407 }
408 else if (mode == gl::PrimitiveMode::LineLoop)
409 {
410 return drawLineLoopArrays(context, first, count, instanceCount);
411 }
412
413 MTLPrimitiveType mtlType = mtl::GetPrimitiveType(mode);
414
415 if (mState.isTransformFeedbackActiveUnpaused())
416 {
417 ANGLE_TRY(setupDraw(context, mode, first, count, instances,
418 gl::DrawElementsType::InvalidEnum, nullptr, true));
419
420 if (instances == 0)
421 {
422 // This method is called from normal drawArrays()
423 mRenderEncoder.draw(mtlType, first, count);
424 }
425 else
426 {
427 execDrawInstanced(mtlType, first, count, instanceCount);
428 }
429 prepareForTransformFeedbackPassTwo();
430 }
431 ANGLE_TRY(setupDraw(context, mode, first, count, instances, gl::DrawElementsType::InvalidEnum,
432 nullptr, false));
433
434 if (instances == 0)
435 {
436 // This method is called from normal drawArrays()
437 mRenderEncoder.draw(mtlType, first, count);
438 }
439 else
440 {
441 execDrawInstanced(mtlType, first, count, instanceCount);
442 }
443
444 return angle::Result::Continue;
445}

479angle::Result ContextMtl::drawTriFanElements(const gl::Context *context,
480 GLsizei count,
481 gl::DrawElementsType type,
482 const void *indices,
483 GLsizei instances)
484{
485 if (count > 3)
486 {
487 mtl::BufferRef genIdxBuffer;
488 uint32_t genIdxBufferOffset;
489 uint32_t genIndicesCount;
490 bool primitiveRestart = getState().isPrimitiveRestartEnabled();
491 ANGLE_TRY(AllocateTriangleFanBufferFromPool(this, count, &mTriFanIndexBuffer, &genIdxBuffer,
492 &genIdxBufferOffset, &genIndicesCount));
493
494 ANGLE_TRY(getDisplay()->getUtils().generateTriFanBufferFromElementsArray(
495 this, {type, count, indices, genIdxBuffer, genIdxBufferOffset, primitiveRestart},
496 &genIndicesCount));
497
498 ANGLE_TRY(mTriFanIndexBuffer.commit(this, false));
499
500 if (mState.isTransformFeedbackActiveUnpaused())
501 {
502 ANGLE_TRY(setupDraw(context, gl::PrimitiveMode::TriangleFan, 0, count, instances, type,
503 indices, true));
504
505 execDrawIndexedInstanced(MTLPrimitiveTypeTriangle, genIndicesCount, MTLIndexTypeUInt32,
506 genIdxBuffer, genIdxBufferOffset, instances);
507 prepareForTransformFeedbackPassTwo();
508 }
509
510 ANGLE_TRY(setupDraw(context, gl::PrimitiveMode::TriangleFan, 0, count, instances, type,
511 indices, false));
512
513 execDrawIndexedInstanced(MTLPrimitiveTypeTriangle, genIndicesCount, MTLIndexTypeUInt32,
514 genIdxBuffer, genIdxBufferOffset, instances);
515
516 return angle::Result::Continue;
517 } // if (count > 3)
518 return drawElementsInstanced(context, gl::PrimitiveMode::Triangles, count, type, indices,
519 instances);
520}

537void ContextMtl::prepareForTransformFeedbackPassTwo()
538{
539 //If we don't have rasterization enabled, we can re-run the same vertex shader. Otherwise,
540 //We need to invalidate the render pipeline state.
541 if(!mState.isRasterizerDiscardEnabled())
542 {
543 invalidateRenderPipeline();
544 }
545}
546angle::Result ContextMtl::drawLineLoopElements(const gl::Context *context,
547 GLsizei count,
548 gl::DrawElementsType type,
549 const void *indices,
550 GLsizei instances)
551{
552 if (count >= 2)
553 {
554 bool primitiveRestart = getState().isPrimitiveRestartEnabled();
555 if (instances <= 1 && !primitiveRestart)
556 {
557 // Non instanced draw and no primitive restart, just use faster version.
558 return drawLineLoopElementsNonInstancedNoPrimitiveRestart(context, count, type,
559 indices);
560 }
561
562 mtl::BufferRef genIdxBuffer;
563 uint32_t genIdxBufferOffset;
564 uint32_t reservedIndices = count * 2;
565 uint32_t genIndicesCount;
566 ANGLE_TRY(AllocateBufferFromPool(this, reservedIndices, &mLineLoopIndexBuffer,
567 &genIdxBuffer, &genIdxBufferOffset));
568
569 ANGLE_TRY(getDisplay()->getUtils().generateLineLoopBufferFromElementsArray(
570 this, {type, count, indices, genIdxBuffer, genIdxBufferOffset, primitiveRestart},
571 &genIndicesCount));
572
573 ANGLE_TRY(mLineLoopIndexBuffer.commit(this, false));
574
575 if (mState.isTransformFeedbackActiveUnpaused())
576 {
577 ANGLE_TRY(setupDraw(context, gl::PrimitiveMode::LineLoop, 0, count, instances, type,
578 indices, true));
579
580 execDrawIndexedInstanced(MTLPrimitiveTypeLineStrip, genIndicesCount, MTLIndexTypeUInt32,
581 genIdxBuffer, genIdxBufferOffset, instances);
582 prepareForTransformFeedbackPassTwo();
583 }
584
585 ANGLE_TRY(setupDraw(context, gl::PrimitiveMode::LineLoop, 0, count, instances, type,
586 indices, false));
587
588 execDrawIndexedInstanced(MTLPrimitiveTypeLineStrip, genIndicesCount, MTLIndexTypeUInt32,
589 genIdxBuffer, genIdxBufferOffset, instances);
590
591 return angle::Result::Continue;
592 } // if (count >= 2)
593 return drawElementsInstanced(context, gl::PrimitiveMode::Lines, count, type, indices,
594 instances);
595}

597angle::Result ContextMtl::drawElementsImpl(const gl::Context *context,
598 gl::PrimitiveMode mode,
599 GLsizei count,
600 gl::DrawElementsType type,
601 const void *indices,
602 GLsizei instances)
603{
604 // Real instances count. Zero means this is not instanced draw.
605 GLsizei instanceCount = instances ? instances : 1;
606 if (mCullAllPolygons && gl::IsPolygonMode(mode))
607 {
608 return angle::Result::Continue;
609 }
610
611 if (mode == gl::PrimitiveMode::TriangleFan)
612 {
613 return drawTriFanElements(context, count, type, indices, instanceCount);
614 }
615 else if (mode == gl::PrimitiveMode::LineLoop)
616 {
617 return drawLineLoopElements(context, count, type, indices, instanceCount);
618 }
619 mtl::BufferRef idxBuffer;
620 mtl::BufferRef drawIdxBuffer;
621 size_t convertedOffset = 0;
622 gl::DrawElementsType convertedType = type;
623 ANGLE_TRY(mVertexArray->getIndexBuffer(context, type, count, indices, &idxBuffer,
624 &convertedOffset, &convertedType));
625
626 ASSERT(idxBuffer);
627 ASSERT((convertedOffset % mtl::kIndexBufferOffsetAlignment) == 0);
628 uint32_t convertedCounti32 = (uint32_t)count;
629
630 if(requiresIndexRewrite(context->getState()))
631 {
632 size_t outIndexCount = 0;
633 gl::PrimitiveMode newMode = gl::PrimitiveMode::InvalidEnum;
634 drawIdxBuffer = mProvokingVertexHelper.preconditionIndexBuffer(mtl::GetImpl(context), idxBuffer, count, convertedOffset, mState.isPrimitiveRestartEnabled(), mode, convertedType, outIndexCount, newMode);
635 if(!drawIdxBuffer)
636 {
637 return angle::Result::Stop;
638 }
639 //Line strips and triangle strips are rewritten to flat line arrays and tri arrays.
640 convertedCounti32 = (uint32_t)outIndexCount;
641 mode = newMode;
642 }
643 else
644 {
645 drawIdxBuffer = idxBuffer;
646 }
647 //Draw commands will only be broken up if transform feedback is enabled,
648 //if the mode is a simple type, and if the buffer contained any restart
649 //indices.
650 const std::vector<DrawCommandRange> drawCommands = mVertexArray->getDrawIndices(context, type, convertedType, mode, convertedCounti32, convertedOffset);
651
652 if (mState.isTransformFeedbackActiveUnpaused())
653 {
654 ANGLE_TRY(setupDraw(context, mode, 0, convertedCounti32, instances, type, indices, true));
655 MTLPrimitiveType mtlType = mtl::GetPrimitiveType(mode);
656
657 MTLIndexType mtlIdxType = mtl::GetIndexType(convertedType);
658
659 if (instances == 0)
660 {
661 // Normal draw
662 for(auto & command : drawCommands)
663 {
664 mRenderEncoder.drawIndexed(mtlType, command.count, mtlIdxType, drawIdxBuffer,
665 command.offset);
666
667 }
668 }
669 else
670 {
671 // Instanced draw
672 for(auto & command : drawCommands)
673 {
674 execDrawIndexedInstanced(mtlType, command.count, mtlIdxType, drawIdxBuffer,
675 command.offset, instanceCount);
676 }
677 }
678 prepareForTransformFeedbackPassTwo();
679 }
680
681 ANGLE_TRY(setupDraw(context, mode, 0, convertedCounti32, instances, type, indices, false));
682
683 MTLPrimitiveType mtlType = mtl::GetPrimitiveType(mode);
684
685 MTLIndexType mtlIdxType = mtl::GetIndexType(convertedType);
686
687 if (instances == 0)
688 {
689 // Normal draw
690 for(auto & command : drawCommands)
691 {
692 mRenderEncoder.drawIndexed(mtlType, command.count, mtlIdxType, drawIdxBuffer,
693 command.offset);
694 }
695 }
696 else
697 {
698 // Instanced draw
699 for(auto & command : drawCommands)
700 {
701 execDrawIndexedInstanced(mtlType, command.count, mtlIdxType, drawIdxBuffer, command.offset,
702 instanceCount);
703 }
704 }
705
706 return angle::Result::Continue;
707}

809void ContextMtl::execDrawInstanced(MTLPrimitiveType primitiveType,
810 uint32_t vertexStart,
811 uint32_t vertexCount,
812 uint32_t instances)
813{
814 if (getDisplay()->getFeatures().hasBaseVertexInstancedDraw.enabled)
815 {
816 mRenderEncoder.drawInstanced(primitiveType, vertexStart, vertexCount, instances);
817 }
818 else
819 {
820 mRenderEncoder.draw(primitiveType, vertexStart, vertexCount);
821 for (uint32_t inst = 1; inst < instances; ++inst)
822 {
823 mDriverUniforms.emulatedInstanceID = inst;
824
825 mRenderEncoder.setVertexData(mDriverUniforms, mtl::kDriverUniformsBindingIndex);
826
827 mVertexArray->emulateInstanceDrawStep(&mRenderEncoder, inst);
828
829 mRenderEncoder.draw(primitiveType, vertexStart, vertexCount);
830 }
831 // Reset instance ID to zero
832 mVertexArray->emulateInstanceDrawStep(&mRenderEncoder, 0);
833 }
834}
835
836void ContextMtl::execDrawIndexedInstanced(MTLPrimitiveType primitiveType,
837 uint32_t indexCount,
838 MTLIndexType indexType,
839 const mtl::BufferRef &indexBuffer,
840 size_t bufferOffset,
841 uint32_t instances)
842{
843 if (getDisplay()->getFeatures().hasBaseVertexInstancedDraw.enabled)
844 {
845 mRenderEncoder.drawIndexedInstanced(primitiveType, indexCount, indexType, indexBuffer,
846 bufferOffset, instances);
847 }
848 else
849 {
850 mRenderEncoder.drawIndexed(primitiveType, indexCount, indexType, indexBuffer, bufferOffset);
851 for (uint32_t inst = 1; inst < instances; ++inst)
852 {
853 mDriverUniforms.emulatedInstanceID = inst;
854
855 mRenderEncoder.setVertexData(mDriverUniforms, mtl::kDriverUniformsBindingIndex);
856
857 mVertexArray->emulateInstanceDrawStep(&mRenderEncoder, inst);
858
859 mRenderEncoder.drawIndexed(primitiveType, indexCount, indexType, indexBuffer,
860 bufferOffset);
861 }
862 // Reset instance ID to zero
863 mVertexArray->emulateInstanceDrawStep(&mRenderEncoder, 0);
864 }
865}

985// State sync with dirty bits.
986angle::Result ContextMtl::syncState(const gl::Context *context,
987 const gl::State::DirtyBits &dirtyBits,
988 const gl::State::DirtyBits &bitMask)
989{
990 const gl::State &glState = context->getState();
991
992 // Initialize incomplete texture set.
993 ANGLE_TRY(ensureIncompleteTexturesCreated(context));
994
995 for (size_t dirtyBit : dirtyBits)
996 {
997 switch (dirtyBit)
998 {
999 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_SCISSOR_TEST_ENABLED:
1000 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_SCISSOR:
1001 updateScissor(glState);
1002 break;
1003 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_VIEWPORT:
1004 {
1005 FramebufferMtl *framebufferMtl = mtl::GetImpl(glState.getDrawFramebuffer());
1006 updateViewport(framebufferMtl, glState.getViewport(), glState.getNearPlane(),
1007 glState.getFarPlane());
1008 // Update the scissor, which will be constrained to the viewport
1009 updateScissor(glState);
1010 break;
1011 }
1012 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_DEPTH_RANGE:
1013 updateDepthRange(glState.getNearPlane(), glState.getFarPlane());
1014 break;
1015 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_BLEND_COLOR:
1016 mDirtyBits.set(DIRTY_BIT_BLEND_COLOR);
1017 break;
1018 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_BLEND_ENABLED:
1019 mBlendDesc.updateBlendEnabled(glState.getBlendState());
1020 invalidateRenderPipeline();
1021 break;
1022 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_BLEND_FUNCS:
1023 mBlendDesc.updateBlendFactors(glState.getBlendState());
1024 invalidateRenderPipeline();
1025 break;
1026 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_BLEND_EQUATIONS:
1027 mBlendDesc.updateBlendOps(glState.getBlendState());
1028 invalidateRenderPipeline();
1029 break;
1030 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_COLOR_MASK:
1031 mBlendDesc.updateWriteMask(glState.getBlendState());
1032 invalidateRenderPipeline();
1033 break;
1034 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_SAMPLE_ALPHA_TO_COVERAGE_ENABLED:
1035 invalidateRenderPipeline();
1036 break;
1037 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_SAMPLE_COVERAGE_ENABLED:
1038 invalidateRenderPipeline();
1039 break;
1040 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_SAMPLE_COVERAGE:
1041 invalidateDriverUniforms();
1042 break;
1043 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_SAMPLE_MASK_ENABLED:
1044 // NOTE(hqle): 3.1 MSAA support
1045 break;
1046 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_SAMPLE_MASK:
1047 // NOTE(hqle): 3.1 MSAA support
1048 break;
1049 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_DEPTH_TEST_ENABLED:
1050 mDepthStencilDesc.updateDepthTestEnabled(glState.getDepthStencilState());
1051 mDirtyBits.set(DIRTY_BIT_DEPTH_STENCIL_DESC);
1052 break;
1053 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_DEPTH_FUNC:
1054 mDepthStencilDesc.updateDepthCompareFunc(glState.getDepthStencilState());
1055 mDirtyBits.set(DIRTY_BIT_DEPTH_STENCIL_DESC);
1056 break;
1057 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_DEPTH_MASK:
1058 mDepthStencilDesc.updateDepthWriteEnabled(glState.getDepthStencilState());
1059 mDirtyBits.set(DIRTY_BIT_DEPTH_STENCIL_DESC);
1060 break;
1061 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_STENCIL_TEST_ENABLED:
1062 mDepthStencilDesc.updateStencilTestEnabled(glState.getDepthStencilState());
1063 mDirtyBits.set(DIRTY_BIT_DEPTH_STENCIL_DESC);
1064 break;
1065 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_STENCIL_FUNCS_FRONT:
1066 mDepthStencilDesc.updateStencilFrontFuncs(glState.getDepthStencilState());
1067 mStencilRefFront = glState.getStencilRef(); // clamped on the frontend
1068 mDirtyBits.set(DIRTY_BIT_DEPTH_STENCIL_DESC);
1069 mDirtyBits.set(DIRTY_BIT_STENCIL_REF);
1070 break;
1071 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_STENCIL_FUNCS_BACK:
1072 mDepthStencilDesc.updateStencilBackFuncs(glState.getDepthStencilState());
1073 mStencilRefBack = glState.getStencilBackRef(); // clamped on the frontend
1074 mDirtyBits.set(DIRTY_BIT_DEPTH_STENCIL_DESC);
1075 mDirtyBits.set(DIRTY_BIT_STENCIL_REF);
1076 break;
1077 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_STENCIL_OPS_FRONT:
1078 mDepthStencilDesc.updateStencilFrontOps(glState.getDepthStencilState());
1079 mDirtyBits.set(DIRTY_BIT_DEPTH_STENCIL_DESC);
1080 break;
1081 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_STENCIL_OPS_BACK:
1082 mDepthStencilDesc.updateStencilBackOps(glState.getDepthStencilState());
1083 mDirtyBits.set(DIRTY_BIT_DEPTH_STENCIL_DESC);
1084 break;
1085 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_STENCIL_WRITEMASK_FRONT:
1086 mDepthStencilDesc.updateStencilFrontWriteMask(glState.getDepthStencilState());
1087 mDirtyBits.set(DIRTY_BIT_DEPTH_STENCIL_DESC);
1088 break;
1089 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_STENCIL_WRITEMASK_BACK:
1090 mDepthStencilDesc.updateStencilBackWriteMask(glState.getDepthStencilState());
1091 mDirtyBits.set(DIRTY_BIT_DEPTH_STENCIL_DESC);
1092 break;
1093 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_CULL_FACE_ENABLED:
1094 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_CULL_FACE:
1095 updateCullMode(glState);
1096 break;
1097 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_FRONT_FACE:
1098 updateFrontFace(glState);
1099 break;
1100 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_POLYGON_OFFSET_FILL_ENABLED:
1101 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_POLYGON_OFFSET:
1102 updateDepthBias(glState);
1103 break;
1104 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_RASTERIZER_DISCARD_ENABLED:
1105 mDirtyBits.set(DIRTY_BIT_RASTERIZER_DISCARD);
1106 break;
1107 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_LINE_WIDTH:
1108 // Do nothing
1109 break;
1110 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_PRIMITIVE_RESTART_ENABLED:
1111 // NOTE(hqle): ES 3.0 feature.
1112 break;
1113 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_CLEAR_COLOR:
1114 mClearColor = mtl::ClearColorValue(
1115 glState.getColorClearValue().red, glState.getColorClearValue().green,
1116 glState.getColorClearValue().blue, glState.getColorClearValue().alpha);
1117 break;
1118 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_CLEAR_DEPTH:
1119 break;
1120 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_CLEAR_STENCIL:
1121 mClearStencil = glState.getStencilClearValue() & mtl::kStencilMaskAll;
1122 break;
1123 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_UNPACK_STATE:
1124 // This is a no-op, its only important to use the right unpack state when we do
1125 // setImage or setSubImage in TextureMtl, which is plumbed through the frontend call
1126 break;
1127 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_UNPACK_BUFFER_BINDING:
1128 break;
1129 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_PACK_STATE:
1130 // This is a no-op, its only important to use the right pack state when we do
1131 // call readPixels later on.
1132 break;
1133 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_PACK_BUFFER_BINDING:
1134 break;
1135 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_DITHER_ENABLED:
1136 break;
1137 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_READ_FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING:
1138 break;
1139 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING:
1140 updateDrawFrameBufferBinding(context);
1141 break;
1142 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_RENDERBUFFER_BINDING:
1143 break;
1144 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_VERTEX_ARRAY_BINDING:
1145 updateVertexArray(context);
1146 break;
1147 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_DRAW_INDIRECT_BUFFER_BINDING:
1148 break;
1149 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_DISPATCH_INDIRECT_BUFFER_BINDING:
1150 break;
1151 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_PROGRAM_BINDING:
1152 mProgram = mtl::GetImpl(glState.getProgram());
1153 break;
1154 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_PROGRAM_EXECUTABLE:
1155 updateProgramExecutable(context);
1156 break;
1157 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_TEXTURE_BINDINGS:
1158 invalidateCurrentTextures();
1159 break;
1160 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_SAMPLER_BINDINGS:
1161 invalidateCurrentTextures();
1162 break;
1163 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BINDING:
1164 // Nothing to do.
1165 break;
1166 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_SHADER_STORAGE_BUFFER_BINDING:
1167 // NOTE(hqle): ES 3.0 feature.
1168 break;
1169 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_UNIFORM_BUFFER_BINDINGS:
1170 mDirtyBits.set(DIRTY_BIT_UNIFORM_BUFFERS_BINDING);
1171 break;
1172 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_ATOMIC_COUNTER_BUFFER_BINDING:
1173 break;
1174 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_IMAGE_BINDINGS:
1175 // NOTE(hqle): properly handle GLSL images.
1176 invalidateCurrentTextures();
1177 break;
1178 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_MULTISAMPLING:
1179 // NOTE(hqle): MSAA on/off.
1180 break;
1181 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_SAMPLE_ALPHA_TO_ONE:
1182 // NOTE(hqle): this is part of EXT_multisample_compatibility.
1183 // NOTE(hqle): MSAA feature.
1184 break;
1185 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_COVERAGE_MODULATION:
1186 break;
1187 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_FRAMEBUFFER_SRGB:
1188 break;
1189 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_CURRENT_VALUES:
1190 {
1191 invalidateDefaultAttributes(glState.getAndResetDirtyCurrentValues());
1192 break;
1193 }
1194 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_PROVOKING_VERTEX:
1195 break;
1196 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_EXTENDED:
1197 updateExtendedState(glState);
1198 break;
1199 case gl::State::DIRTY_BIT_SAMPLE_SHADING:
1200 // Nothing to do until OES_sample_shading is implemented.
1201 break;
1202 default:
1203 UNREACHABLE();
1204 break;
1205 }
1206 }
1207
1208 return angle::Result::Continue;
1209}

1376
1377angle::Result ContextMtl::onBeginTransformFeedback(
1378 size_t bufferCount,
1379 const gl::TransformFeedbackBuffersArray<BufferMtl *> &buffers)
1380{
1381 onTransformFeedbackStateChanged();
1382
1383 for (size_t bufferIndex = 0; bufferIndex < bufferCount; ++bufferIndex)
1384 {
1385 if (mCurrentTransformFeedbackBuffers.count(buffers[bufferIndex]) != 0)
1386 {
1387 endEncoding(mRenderEncoder);
1388 break;
1389 }
1390 }
1391
1392 populateTransformFeedbackBufferSet(bufferCount, buffers);
1393
1394 return angle::Result::Continue;
1395}
1396
1397void ContextMtl::populateTransformFeedbackBufferSet(
1398 size_t bufferCount,
1399 const gl::TransformFeedbackBuffersArray<BufferMtl *> &buffers)
1400{
1401 for (size_t bufferIndex = 0; bufferIndex < bufferCount; ++bufferIndex)
1402 {
1403 mCurrentTransformFeedbackBuffers.insert(buffers[bufferIndex]);
1404 }
1405}
1406
1407void ContextMtl::onEndTransformFeedback()
1408{
1409 if (getDisplay()->getFeatures().emulateTransformFeedback.enabled)
1410 {
1411 onTransformFeedbackStateChanged();
1412 }
1413 if (getDisplay()->getFeatures().hasExplicitMemBarrier.enabled)
1414 {
1415 const gl::ProgramExecutable *executable = mState.getProgramExecutable();
1416 ASSERT(executable);
1417 ASSERT(executable->hasTransformFeedbackOutput() || mState.isTransformFeedbackActive());
1418 TransformFeedbackMtl *transformFeedbackMtl = mtl::GetImpl(mState.getCurrentTransformFeedback());
1419 size_t bufferCount = executable->getTransformFeedbackBufferCount();
1420 const gl::TransformFeedbackBuffersArray<BufferMtl *> &bufferHandles =
1421 transformFeedbackMtl->getBufferHandles();
1422 for (size_t i = 0; i < bufferCount; i++)
1423 {
1424 const mtl::BufferRef & constBufferRef = bufferHandles[i]->getCurrentBuffer();
1425 mRenderEncoder.memoryBarrierWithResource(constBufferRef, mtl::kRenderStageVertex, mtl::kRenderStageVertex);
1426 }
1427 }
1428 else
1429 {
1430 //End the command encoder, so any Transform Feedback changes are available to subsequent draw calls.
1431 endEncoding(false);
1432 }
1433}

1436{
1437 if (getDisplay()->getFeatures().emulateTransformFeedback.enabled)
1438 {
1439 onTransformFeedbackStateChanged();
1440 }
1441 return angle::Result::Continue;
1442}

1589void ContextMtl::endRenderEncoding(mtl::RenderCommandEncoder *encoder)
1590{
1591 // End any pending visibility query in the render pass
1592 if (mOcclusionQuery)
1593 {
1594 disableActiveOcclusionQueryInRenderPass();
1595 }
1596
1597 encoder->endEncoding();
1598
1599 // Resolve visibility results
1600 mOcclusionQueryPool.resolveVisibilityResults(this);
1601
1602 mCurrentTransformFeedbackBuffers.clear();
1603
1604 // Reset serials for XFB if active.
1605 if (mState.isTransformFeedbackActiveUnpaused())
1606 {
1607 const gl::ProgramExecutable *executable = mState.getProgramExecutable();
1608 ASSERT(executable);
1609 size_t xfbBufferCount = executable->getTransformFeedbackBufferCount();
1610
1611 TransformFeedbackMtl *transformFeedbackMtl =
1612 mtl::GetImpl(mState.getCurrentTransformFeedback());
1613
1614 populateTransformFeedbackBufferSet(xfbBufferCount,
1615 transformFeedbackMtl->getBufferHandles());
1616 }
1617}

1633 {
1634 mBlitEncoder.endEncoding();

1639 mComputeEncoder.endEncoding();

1693
1694mtl::RenderCommandEncoder *ContextMtl::getRenderPassCommandEncoder(const mtl::RenderPassDesc &desc)
1695{
1696 if (hasStartedRenderPass(desc))
1697 {
1698 return &mRenderEncoder;
1699 }
1700
1701 endEncoding(false);
1702
1703 ensureCommandBufferReady();
1704
1705 // Need to re-apply everything on next draw call.
1706 mDirtyBits.set();
1707
1708 id<MTLDevice> metalDevice = getDisplay()->getMetalDevice();
1709 if (mtl::DeviceHasMaximumRenderTargetSize(metalDevice))
1710 {
1711 MTLRenderPassDescriptor *objCDesc = [MTLRenderPassDescriptor renderPassDescriptor];
1712 desc.convertToMetalDesc(objCDesc);
1713 NSUInteger maxSize = mtl::GetMaxRenderTargetSizeForDeviceInBytes(metalDevice);
1714 NSUInteger renderTargetSize =
1715 ComputeTotalSizeUsedForMTLRenderPassDescriptor(objCDesc, this, metalDevice);
1716 if (renderTargetSize > maxSize)
1717 {
1718 NSString *errorString =
1719 [NSString stringWithFormat:@"This set of render targets requires %lu bytes of "
1720 @"pixel storage. This device supports %lu bytes.",
1721 (unsigned long)renderTargetSize, (unsigned long)maxSize];
1722 NSError *err = [NSError errorWithDomain:@"MTLValidationError"
1723 code:-1
1724 userInfo:@{NSLocalizedDescriptionKey : errorString}];
1725 this->handleError(err, __FILE__, ANGLE_FUNCTION, __LINE__);
1726 return nil;
1727 }
1728 }
1729 return &mRenderEncoder.restart(desc);
1730}

1732// Utilities to quickly create render command encoder to a specific texture:
1733// The previous content of texture will be loaded
1734mtl::RenderCommandEncoder *ContextMtl::getTextureRenderCommandEncoder(
1735 const mtl::TextureRef &textureTarget,

1737{
1738 ASSERT(textureTarget && textureTarget->valid());

1745 index.hasLayer() ? index.getLayerIndex() : 0;

1849void ContextMtl::updateScissor(const gl::State &glState)
1850{
1851 FramebufferMtl *framebufferMtl = mtl::GetImpl(glState.getDrawFramebuffer());
1852 gl::Rectangle renderArea = framebufferMtl->getCompleteRenderArea();
1853
1854 ANGLE_MTL_LOG("renderArea = %d,%d,%d,%d", renderArea.x, renderArea.y, renderArea.width,
1855 renderArea.height);
1856
1857 // Clip the render area to the viewport.
1858 gl::Rectangle viewportClippedRenderArea;
1859 if (!gl::ClipRectangle(renderArea, glState.getViewport(), &viewportClippedRenderArea))
1860 {
1861 viewportClippedRenderArea = gl::Rectangle();
1862 }
1863
1864 gl::Rectangle scissoredArea = ClipRectToScissor(getState(), viewportClippedRenderArea, false);
1865 if (framebufferMtl->flipY())
1866 {
1867 scissoredArea.y = renderArea.height - scissoredArea.y - scissoredArea.height;
1868 }
1869
1870 ANGLE_MTL_LOG("scissoredArea = %d,%d,%d,%d", scissoredArea.x, scissoredArea.y,
1871 scissoredArea.width, scissoredArea.height);
1872
1873 mScissorRect = mtl::GetScissorRect(scissoredArea);
1874 mDirtyBits.set(DIRTY_BIT_SCISSOR);
1875}

1877void ContextMtl::updateCullMode(const gl::State &glState)
1878{
1879 const gl::RasterizerState &rasterState = glState.getRasterizerState();
1880
1881 mCullAllPolygons = false;
1882 if (!rasterState.cullFace)
1883 {
1884 mCullMode = MTLCullModeNone;
1885 }
1886 else
1887 {
1888 switch (rasterState.cullMode)
1889 {
1890 case gl::CullFaceMode::Back:
1891 mCullMode = MTLCullModeBack;
1892 break;
1893 case gl::CullFaceMode::Front:
1894 mCullMode = MTLCullModeFront;
1895 break;
1896 case gl::CullFaceMode::FrontAndBack:
1897 mCullAllPolygons = true;
1898 break;
1899 default:
1900 UNREACHABLE();
1901 break;
1902 }
1903 }
1904
1905 mDirtyBits.set(DIRTY_BIT_CULL_MODE);
1906}

1941void ContextMtl::onDrawFrameBufferChangedState(const gl::Context *context,
1942 FramebufferMtl *framebuffer,
1943 bool renderPassChanged)
1944{
1945 const gl::State &glState = getState();
1946 ASSERT(framebuffer == mtl::GetImpl(glState.getDrawFramebuffer()));
1947
1948 updateViewport(framebuffer, glState.getViewport(), glState.getNearPlane(),
1949 glState.getFarPlane());
1950 updateFrontFace(glState);
1951 updateScissor(glState);
1952
1953 if (renderPassChanged)
1954 {
1955 // End any render encoding using the old render pass.
1956 endEncoding(false);
1957 // Need to re-apply state to RenderCommandEncoder
1958 invalidateState(context);
1959 }
1960 else
1961 {
1962 // Invalidate current pipeline only.
1963 invalidateRenderPipeline();
1964 }
1965}

1982angle::Result ContextMtl::onOcclusionQueryBegan(const gl::Context *context, QueryMtl *query)
1983{
1984 ASSERT(mOcclusionQuery == nullptr);
1985 mOcclusionQuery = query;
1986
1987 if (mRenderEncoder.valid())
1988 {
1989 // if render pass has started, start the query in the encoder
1990 return startOcclusionQueryInRenderPass(query, true);
1991 }
1992 else
1993 {
1994 query->resetVisibilityResult(this);
1995 }
1996
1997 return angle::Result::Continue;

1999void ContextMtl::onOcclusionQueryEnded(const gl::Context *context, QueryMtl *query)
2000{
2001 ASSERT(mOcclusionQuery == query);
2002
2003 if (mRenderEncoder.valid())
2004 {
2005 // if render pass has started, end the query in the encoder
2006 disableActiveOcclusionQueryInRenderPass();
2007 }
2008
2009 mOcclusionQuery = nullptr;
2010}
2011void ContextMtl::onOcclusionQueryDestroyed(const gl::Context *context, QueryMtl *query)
2012{
2013 if (query->getAllocatedVisibilityOffsets().empty())
2014 {
2015 return;
2016 }
2017 if (mOcclusionQuery == query)
2018 {
2019 onOcclusionQueryEnded(context, query);
2020 }
2021 mOcclusionQueryPool.deallocateQueryOffset(this, query);
2022}
2023
2024void ContextMtl::disableActiveOcclusionQueryInRenderPass()
2025{
2026 if (!mOcclusionQuery || mOcclusionQuery->getAllocatedVisibilityOffsets().empty())
2027 {
2028 return;
2029 }
2030
2031 ASSERT(mRenderEncoder.valid());
2032 mRenderEncoder.setVisibilityResultMode(MTLVisibilityResultModeDisabled,
2033 mOcclusionQuery->getAllocatedVisibilityOffsets().back());
2034}
2035
2036angle::Result ContextMtl::restartActiveOcclusionQueryInRenderPass()
2037{
2038 if (!mOcclusionQuery || mOcclusionQuery->getAllocatedVisibilityOffsets().empty())
2039 {
2040 return angle::Result::Continue;
2041 }
2042
2043 return startOcclusionQueryInRenderPass(mOcclusionQuery, false);
2044}
2045
2046angle::Result ContextMtl::startOcclusionQueryInRenderPass(QueryMtl *query, bool clearOldValue)
2047{
2048 ASSERT(mRenderEncoder.valid());
2049
2050 ANGLE_TRY(mOcclusionQueryPool.allocateQueryOffset(this, query, clearOldValue));
2051
2052 mRenderEncoder.setVisibilityResultMode(MTLVisibilityResultModeBoolean,
2053 query->getAllocatedVisibilityOffsets().back());
2054
2055 // We need to mark the query's buffer as being written in this command buffer now. Since the
2056 // actual writing is deferred until the render pass ends and user could try to read the query
2057 // result before the render pass ends.
2058 mCmdBuffer.setWriteDependency(query->getVisibilityResultBuffer());
2059
2060 return angle::Result::Continue;
2061}

2097angle::Result ContextMtl::updateDefaultAttribute(size_t attribIndex)
2098{
2099 const gl::State &glState = mState;
2100 const gl::VertexAttribCurrentValueData &defaultValue =
2101 glState.getVertexAttribCurrentValues()[attribIndex];
2102

2104 sizeof(gl::VertexAttribCurrentValueData::Values);
2105
2106 static_assert(kDefaultGLAttributeValueSize == mtl::kDefaultAttributeSize,
2107 "Unexpected default attribute size");

2109 mtl::kDefaultAttributeSize);

2113
2114angle::Result ContextMtl::setupDraw(const gl::Context *context,
2115 gl::PrimitiveMode mode,
2116 GLint firstVertex,
2117 GLsizei vertexOrIndexCount,
2118 GLsizei instances,
2119 gl::DrawElementsType indexTypeOrNone,
2120 const void *indices,
2121 bool transformFeedbackDraw)
2122{
2123 ASSERT(mProgram);
2124
2125 // Update transform feedback offsets on every draw call.
2126 if (mState.isTransformFeedbackActiveUnpaused())
2127 {
2128 ASSERT(firstVertex != -1);
2129 mXfbBaseVertex = firstVertex;
2130 mXfbVertexCountPerInstance = vertexOrIndexCount;
2131 invalidateDriverUniforms();
2132 }
2133
2134 // instances=0 means no instanced draw.
2135 GLsizei instanceCount = instances ? instances : 1;
2136
2137 if (context->getStateCache().hasAnyActiveClientAttrib())
2138 {

2153 invalidateState(context);

2157 {
2158 // Start new render command encoder
2159 ANGLE_MTL_TRY(this, mDrawFramebuffer->ensureRenderPassStarted(context));
2160
2161 // re-apply everything
2162 invalidateState(context);
2163 }

2165 if (mOcclusionQuery && mOcclusionQueryPool.getNumRenderPassAllocatedQueries() == 0)
2166 {
2167 // The occlusion query is still active, and a new render pass has started.
2168 // We need to continue the querying process in the new render encoder.
2169 ANGLE_TRY(startOcclusionQueryInRenderPass(mOcclusionQuery, false));
2170 }
2171
2172 bool changedPipeline;
2173 ANGLE_TRY(checkIfPipelineChanged(context, mode, mState.isTransformFeedbackActive(),
2174 &changedPipeline));
2175
2176 bool uniformBuffersDirty = false;

2178 {
2179 switch (bit)
2180 {
2181 case DIRTY_BIT_TEXTURES:
2182 // Already handled.
2183 break;
2184 case DIRTY_BIT_DEFAULT_ATTRIBS:
2185 ANGLE_TRY(handleDirtyDefaultAttribs(context));
2186 break;
2187 case DIRTY_BIT_DRIVER_UNIFORMS:
2188 ANGLE_TRY(handleDirtyDriverUniforms(context, firstVertex, vertexOrIndexCount));
2189 break;
2190 case DIRTY_BIT_DEPTH_STENCIL_DESC:
2191 ANGLE_TRY(handleDirtyDepthStencilState(context));
2192 break;
2193 case DIRTY_BIT_DEPTH_BIAS:
2194 ANGLE_TRY(handleDirtyDepthBias(context));
2195 break;
2196 case DIRTY_BIT_STENCIL_REF:
2197 mRenderEncoder.setStencilRefVals(mStencilRefFront, mStencilRefBack);
2198 break;
2199 case DIRTY_BIT_BLEND_COLOR:
2200 mRenderEncoder.setBlendColor(
2201 mState.getBlendColor().red, mState.getBlendColor().green,
2202 mState.getBlendColor().blue, mState.getBlendColor().alpha);
2203 break;
2204 case DIRTY_BIT_VIEWPORT:
2205 mRenderEncoder.setViewport(mViewport);
2206 break;
2207 case DIRTY_BIT_SCISSOR:
2208 mRenderEncoder.setScissorRect(mScissorRect);
2209 break;
2210 case DIRTY_BIT_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER:
2211 // Already handled.
2212 break;
2213 case DIRTY_BIT_CULL_MODE:
2214 mRenderEncoder.setCullMode(mCullMode);
2215 break;
2216 case DIRTY_BIT_WINDING:
2217 mRenderEncoder.setFrontFacingWinding(mWinding);
2218 break;
2219 case DIRTY_BIT_RENDER_PIPELINE:
2220 // Already handled. See checkIfPipelineChanged().
2221 break;
2222 case DIRTY_BIT_UNIFORM_BUFFERS_BINDING:
2223 uniformBuffersDirty = true;
2224 break;
2225 case DIRTY_BIT_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BUFFERS:
2226 ANGLE_TRY(handleDirtyGraphicsTransformFeedbackBuffersEmulation(context));
2227 break;
2228 case DIRTY_BIT_RASTERIZER_DISCARD:
2229 break;
2230 default:
2231 UNREACHABLE();
2232 break;
2233 }
2234 }
2235
2236
2237
2238 if (transformFeedbackDraw)
2239 {
2240 mtl::RenderUtils &utils = getDisplay()->getUtils();
2241 angle::Result result =
2242 utils.createTransformFeedbackPSO(context, &mRenderEncoder, mRenderPipelineDesc);
2243 ANGLE_UNUSED_VARIABLE(result);
2244 assert(result == angle::Result::Continue);
2245 changedPipeline = true;
2246 }
2247
2248 ANGLE_TRY(mProgram->setupDraw(context, &mRenderEncoder, mRenderPipelineDesc,
2249 changedPipeline, textureChanged,
2250 uniformBuffersDirty, transformFeedbackDraw));
2251
2252 // Setting up the draw required us to call a command buffer flush, re-run setupDraw with state invaliated to restart the command buffer from the current draw with previously set state
2253 if (!mCmdBuffer.valid())
2254 {
2255 invalidateState(context);
2256 ANGLE_TRY(setupDraw(context, mode, firstVertex, vertexOrIndexCount, instances, indexTypeOrNone, indices, transformFeedbackDraw));
2257 }

2305angle::Result ContextMtl::handleDirtyDriverUniforms(const gl::Context *context,
2306 GLint drawCallFirstVertex,
2307 uint32_t verticesPerInstance)
2308{
2309 const gl::Rectangle &glViewport = mState.getViewport();
2310
2311 float depthRangeNear = mState.getNearPlane();
2312 float depthRangeFar = mState.getFarPlane();
2313 float depthRangeDiff = depthRangeFar - depthRangeNear;
2314
2315 mDriverUniforms.viewport[0] = glViewport.x;
2316 mDriverUniforms.viewport[1] = glViewport.y;
2317 mDriverUniforms.viewport[2] = glViewport.width;
2318 mDriverUniforms.viewport[3] = glViewport.height;
2319
2320 mDriverUniforms.halfRenderArea[0] =
2321 static_cast<float>(mDrawFramebuffer->getState().getDimensions().width) * 0.5f;
2322 mDriverUniforms.halfRenderArea[1] =
2323 static_cast<float>(mDrawFramebuffer->getState().getDimensions().height) * 0.5f;
2324 mDriverUniforms.flipXY[0] = 1.0f;
2325 mDriverUniforms.flipXY[1] = mDrawFramebuffer->flipY() ? -1.0f : 1.0f;
2326 mDriverUniforms.negFlipXY[0] = mDriverUniforms.flipXY[0];
2327 mDriverUniforms.negFlipXY[1] = -mDriverUniforms.flipXY[1];
2328
2329 // gl_ClipDistance
2330 mDriverUniforms.enabledClipDistances = mState.getEnabledClipDistances().bits();
2331
2332 mDriverUniforms.depthRange[0] = depthRangeNear;
2333 mDriverUniforms.depthRange[1] = depthRangeFar;
2334 mDriverUniforms.depthRange[2] = depthRangeDiff;
2335 mDriverUniforms.depthRange[3] = NeedToInvertDepthRange(depthRangeNear, depthRangeFar) ? -1 : 1;

2346 coverageMask = sampleMask & (~coverageMask);

2360 mDriverUniforms.xfbBufferOffsets.data(),
2361 mDriverUniforms.xfbBufferOffsets.size());

2444angle::Result ContextMtl::checkIfPipelineChanged(const gl::Context *context,
2445 gl::PrimitiveMode primitiveMode,
2446 bool xbfPass,
2447 bool *pipelineDescChanged)
2448{
2449 ASSERT(mRenderEncoder.valid());
2450 mtl::PrimitiveTopologyClass topologyClass = mtl::GetPrimitiveTopologyClass(primitiveMode);
2451
2452 bool rppChange = mDirtyBits.test(DIRTY_BIT_RENDER_PIPELINE) ||
2453 topologyClass != mRenderPipelineDesc.inputPrimitiveTopology;
2454
2455 // Obtain RenderPipelineDesc's vertex array descriptor.
2456 ANGLE_TRY(mVertexArray->setupDraw(context, &mRenderEncoder, &rppChange,
2457 &mRenderPipelineDesc.vertexDescriptor));
2458
2459 if (rppChange)
2460 {
2461 const mtl::RenderPassDesc &renderPassDesc = mRenderEncoder.renderPassDesc();
2462 // Obtain RenderPipelineDesc's output descriptor.
2463 renderPassDesc.populateRenderPipelineOutputDesc(mBlendDesc,
2464 &mRenderPipelineDesc.outputDescriptor);
2465
2466 mRenderPipelineDesc.inputPrimitiveTopology = topologyClass;
2467 mRenderPipelineDesc.rasterizationType =
2468 (mState.isRasterizerDiscardEnabled() ? mtl::RenderPipelineRasterization::EmulatedDiscard
2469 : mtl::RenderPipelineRasterization::Enabled);
2470 mRenderPipelineDesc.alphaToCoverageEnabled = mState.isSampleAlphaToCoverageEnabled();
2471 mRenderPipelineDesc.emulateCoverageMask = mState.isSampleCoverageEnabled();
2472
2473 mRenderPipelineDesc.outputDescriptor.updateEnabledDrawBuffers(
2474 mDrawFramebuffer->getState().getEnabledDrawBuffers());
2475 }
